➡️ Bitcoin & Litecoin: Halvings every ~4 years (latest: BTC in Apr 2024, LTC in Aug 2023). 
➡️ Dogecoin: No halving. Fixed reward of 10,000 DOGE/block = inflationary. 
➡️ Kaspa: No halving, but monthly emission reduction—gradual, not abrupt.

⛏️ Difficulty Adjustments: 
➡️ Bitcoin: Adjusts every 2 weeks. 
➡️ Litecoin/Dogecoin: Adjust every block. 
➡️ Kaspa: Adjusts dynamically every second.

⚙️ Comparing Hardware & Algorithms: 
➡️ Bitcoin uses SHA-256, requiring high TH/s output. ➡️ Litecoin & Dogecoin run on the Scrypt algorithm and benefit from merged mining—mine one, earn both.
